Ranche Ghar

I recently had lunch at Ranche Ghar and had a pleasant experience. The menu offered a variety of seafood options, and I opted for the Fish Thali, Prawns, and Chonak Thali.

The taste of the dishes was good, but the fish curry could have been improved. However, the other dishes, such as the Tisrio and Crab Curry, were delicious.

The ambiance was lovely, making for a comfortable dining experience.

The prices were pocket-friendly, offering great value for money.

The service was good, with friendly staff attending to our needs.

Ample parking space was available, making it convenient for customers.

Overall, I would recommend Ranche Ghar for its good food, lovely ambiance, and affordable prices.

Visited   this place for lunch after searching for a new restaurant serving fish thali. We tried  their Special Fish Thali (King fish) Rs 300 . Normal thali prawns rs 220.All the items served were well made n delicious.
Ambience was good and ample seating space.
Service was quick and prompt. Would definitely recommend to visit this place and try out the various  items in their menu. Good job please keep it up.

We ordered the King Fish Thali, Squids Better Fry, and Lime Soda. The first thing that stood out negatively was the inclusion of chapati in the fish thali. In a traditional Goan fish thali, chapati is not served. Additionally, the prawns curry in the thali lacked flavor and was quite disappointing. The highlight of any Goan fish thali is usually the curry, but unfortunately, the curry here didn’t meet expectations.

The Squids Better Fry was decent, though I wouldn’t describe it as extraordinary—just an average taste.

Overall, I felt the place is somewhat overrated. For the same price, there are plenty of other establishments that offer a better dining experience with superior flavors.
